         <abstract>
            <p>A new way to define linear multistep methods for functional differential equations is presented, and some of their properties are analyzed. The asymptotic behavior of the global discretization error is investigated. Finally, Milne's device is generalized to functional differential equations. The effect of the nonsmoothness of the exact solution is taken into account.</p>
          </abstract>
